            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is conjectured from the printed stationery, with ‘<hi rend="italic">Bromley</hi>’ deleted and ‘Beckenham’ added by hand, which was a form used by CD between April 1869 and May 1871, and by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7626.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Francis Darwin, 25 March [1871]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5982.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Henry Jackson</ref>; see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7420.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Francis Darwin, [before 22 April 1871?]</ref> and n. 2.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD discussed physical expressions of prayer and reverence in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, pp. 220–1, and shrugging in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, pp. 264–72. For a summary of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5918.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Thomas Hobbes’s</ref> remarks on laughter, see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2399.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ewin 2001</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">‘Ciconia’ is probably a mistake for ‘Cistercians’; CD cited <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4838.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Edward Burnett Tylor’s</ref> comments in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7901.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Tylor 1871</ref> on Cistercian gesture-language in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, p. 61.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">CD discussed laughter in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, pp. 198–221.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7626.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Francis Darwin, 25 March [1871]</ref>.</note>
